Sentencas: The perovskite series, La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-delta (x = 0.2, 0.3, 0.4, 0.5, 0.67, LSCrFe), was synthesized and examined as both single phase and LSCrFe-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-beta (GDC) composite solid oxide fuel cell anodes in full cells with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-epsilon/La0.4Ce0.6O2 bilayer electrolytes.
Titulo: Stable, Low Polarization Resistance Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anodes: La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.2-0.67)

Sentencas: Each anode demonstrated marked improvement in polarization resistance compared to prior studies on Fe-free La1-xSrxCrO3-delta-based anodes and in stability compared to studies on more Fe-rich compositions.
Titulo: Stable, Low Polarization Resistance Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anodes: La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.2-0.67)

Sentencas: Higher Fe content anodes yielded lower polarization resistances, with the x = 0.67 anodes obtaining resistances of 0.275 Omega.cm(2) for LSCrFe and 0.333 Omega.
Titulo: Stable, Low Polarization Resistance Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anodes: La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.2-0.67)

Sentencas: cm(2) for LSCrFe-GDC in humidified H-2 at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Stable, Low Polarization Resistance Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anodes: La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.2-0.67)

Sentencas: The lower polarization resistance with increasing Fe content can be attributed to oxygen loss, which introduces significant ionic conductivity into these perovskites.
Titulo: Stable, Low Polarization Resistance Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anodes: La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.2-0.67)

Sentencas: Substitution of an intermediate amount of Fe and Sr into the perovskites can thus optimize anode performance.
Titulo: Stable, Low Polarization Resistance Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anodes: La1-xSrxCr1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.2-0.67)
